-RINGMASTER: Hey, folks,
make sure

22:37.045 --> 22:38.447
to take your familiar corpses
with you as you leave.

22:44.125 --> 22:46.463
One moment,
I'll be right with you, Xerxes.

22:46.497 --> 22:48.935
-(whispering)
-So...

22:48.968 --> 22:51.073
we went to the night market
last night.

22:51.106 --> 22:54.547
Oh, my, the night market,
what fun.

22:54.580 --> 22:57.018
-Mm.
-I already had plans last night,

22:57.051 --> 22:59.222
so it's a good thing
I didn't get invited.

22:59.255 --> 23:01.326
And, here, I got you a gift.

23:01.359 --> 23:04.533
It came with these weird vials
of whatever this is.

23:04.567 --> 23:07.438
I think I'll probably
just keep all of these.

23:07.472 --> 23:10.177
And you can use the box to store
your brooches or whatever.

23:10.211 --> 23:12.950
This is for me? This is so kind.

23:12.983 --> 23:15.221
I am very kind.
Very good boss.

23:15.254 --> 23:17.458
GUIDE:
I cannot remember the last time

23:17.493 --> 23:19.329
someone got me a gift.

23:19.362 --> 23:21.099
And I do have a lot of brooches.

23:21.133 --> 23:23.905
-I didn't think
anyone noticed...
-Oh!

23:23.938 --> 23:25.241
You have detected

23:25.274 --> 23:27.278
the sweet,
intoxicating scent of the...

23:27.311 --> 23:29.449
(inhales deeply)
Water Lily of The Nile.

23:29.482 --> 23:31.687
-Haven't you, Xerxes?
-Uh-oh.

23:31.721 --> 23:33.090
NADJA:
Water Lily

23:33.123 --> 23:34.159
of the Nile.

23:34.192 --> 23:35.261
That is what they call it.

23:35.294 --> 23:36.998
It's a medicinal flower.

23:37.031 --> 23:39.002
It's a narcotic
that the Egyptians

23:39.035 --> 23:41.072
used to bury
with their dead in order

23:41.106 --> 23:43.410
to help ease the sufferings
of the afterlife.

23:43.444 --> 23:45.982
And according
to the Compendium Narcoticum,

23:46.016 --> 23:48.621
-LASZLO:
Some third-rate cobbler...
-it is the only drug

23:48.655 --> 23:50.625
that helps with the pain
of being a wraith.

23:50.659 --> 23:52.261
Very hard to come by.

23:52.295 --> 23:54.065
And it is said

23:54.099 --> 23:56.537
that those little gobshites
will do anything for it.

23:57.539 --> 24:01.146
Do I have enough of these to
give to all of the wraiths? No.

24:01.179 --> 24:03.685
Do I have enough of these
to give to the one wraith

24:03.718 --> 24:06.223
who tells all the other wraiths
what to do?

24:06.256 --> 24:08.227
Maybe.

24:08.260 --> 24:11.233
I think that is probably
all I need.

24:11.266 --> 24:13.170
Don't you?!

24:13.203 --> 24:15.007
GUIDE:
He won't do it.

24:15.040 --> 24:16.644
Union solidarity
is a big deal to them.

24:16.677 --> 24:18.515
"We have a deal."

24:18.548 --> 24:20.484
There you go. Pleasure
doing business with you.

24:20.519 --> 24:22.121
That's how it's done.

24:23.423 --> 24:26.363
-(indistinct whispering)
-GUIDE:
I don't think they're happy.

24:26.396 --> 24:30.204
NADJA:
If they all vote,
he can overrule them, right?

24:30.237 --> 24:32.643
-What?
-(Guide gasps)

24:32.676 --> 24:34.012
GUIDE:
Oh!

24:34.045 --> 24:36.717
GUIDE:
Oh, no!

24:36.751 --> 24:38.755
Mm, shit, shit, shit.

24:38.788 --> 24:42.161
"Xerxes is no longer our leader.

24:42.195 --> 24:45.134
Also, he is dead."
Obviously.

24:45.167 --> 24:46.637
Fine! Fuck it!

24:46.671 --> 24:48.708
You can have Mondays off
with pay.

24:48.741 --> 24:50.244
And I will build you five

24:50.277 --> 24:52.114
new supply closets
for you to sleep in.

24:53.417 --> 24:55.287
-(groans)
-(chuckles)

24:55.321 --> 24:56.724
(spits)

24:56.757 --> 24:58.995
-Now get back to work!
-(indistinct whispers)

25:01.266 --> 25:03.003
There we go.

25:03.036 --> 25:04.573
I know you've had
a disappointing day,

25:04.607 --> 25:07.144
so no rehearsal tonight.

25:07.178 --> 25:09.583
Would you like me to read one
of your fairy stories to you?

25:09.617 --> 25:11.453
Uh, that's okay.
I-I don't think

25:11.486 --> 25:13.658
I want to read those anymore.

25:13.691 --> 25:15.795
Maybe, can you read me something

25:15.829 --> 25:18.333
from one of your real books
about real stuff?

25:18.367 --> 25:20.271
I thought you'd never ask.

25:20.304 --> 25:22.509
(laughs)

25:22.543 --> 25:25.414
One of my personal favorites.
Oh, yes.

25:25.447 --> 25:28.186
"The village of Holcomb stands

25:28.220 --> 25:31.494
"on the high
wheat plains of western Kansas,

25:31.527 --> 25:35.067
a lonesome area that other
Kansans call 'out there.'"

25:35.100 --> 25:37.338
-Are you still awake?
-Um, yeah.

25:37.371 --> 25:39.610
It gets very heavy
from here on in.

25:39.643 --> 25:43.450
♪ This little piggy
went to market ♪

25:43.483 --> 25:48.193
♪ And this little piggy
stayed home ♪

25:48.227 --> 25:52.468
♪ This little piggy
had roast beef ♪

25:52.502 --> 25:56.811
♪ This little piggy had none ♪

25:57.813 --> 25:59.415
♪ How I recall ♪

25:59.449 --> 26:02.321
♪ My dear old mother ♪

26:02.355 --> 26:07.064
♪ Putting me to bed ♪

26:07.098 --> 26:10.839
♪ She tucked me in and said ♪

26:10.872 --> 26:15.749
♪ To her little sleepyhead ♪

26:15.782 --> 26:18.420
♪ This little piggy ♪

26:18.453 --> 26:22.596
♪ Stayed home. ♪

